text.section:
The fastening of a load to a vehicle shall be:
By two separate common coil B.B. chains, the links of which may not be less than:
3/8 of an inch in diameter for loads of 3 tons or less; or
1/2 of an inch in diameter for loads over 3 tons;
If they have at least as much tensile strength as the chains, by:
Wire rope not less than 5/16 of an inch in diameter;
Steel strapping;
Logistic webbing of synthetic fibers; or
Any fastening device specified in regulations adopted jointly by the Administration and the Department of State Police; or
As specified in Part 393.102(b) (securement systems) of the federal Motor Carrier Safety Regulations.
